957
01:03:00.985 --> 01:03:04.447
We went to the first hearing
and sat with their family.

958
01:03:04.947 --> 01:03:05.907
Yep.

959
01:03:06.449 --> 01:03:08.034
Sat with the Shirillas?

960
01:03:08.117 --> 01:03:09.619
Mm-hmm.

961
01:03:11.412 --> 01:03:15.374
We still thought she had been drinking
or there were drugs involved.

962
01:03:16.042 --> 01:03:19.378
You know. they were kids.
Accidents happen all the time like that.

963
01:03:19.462 --> 01:03:21.214
You never in a million years think

964
01:03:22.215 --> 01:03:24.383
this girl killed your brother.

965
01:03:24.967 --> 01:03:26.135
You just don't think that way.

966
01:03:29.806 --> 01:03:35.144
All of the records will show.
from when the police first responded.

967
01:03:35.228 --> 01:03:39.273
she had no recollection of the events.

968
01:03:39.357 --> 01:03:43.528
and that is consistent
with what happens many times in accidents.

969
01:03:44.487 --> 01:03:50.618
My attorney was very reassuring
of there being no evidence

970
01:03:50.701 --> 01:03:54.622
and that anyone can see
that there was no intent.

971
01:03:54.705 --> 01:04:00.461
How can you come to any conclusion
other than. if anything. she's reckless?

972
01:04:02.046 --> 01:04:05.299
Your Honor. at issue
in this case. primarily.

973
01:04:05.383 --> 01:04:08.970
is the defendant's state of mind
at the time of the fatal crash.

974
01:04:09.554 --> 01:04:11.639
The evidence in this case is clear.

975
01:04:12.223 --> 01:04:14.141
She drove the car into the wall.

976
01:04:14.225 --> 01:04:17.019
She made up her mind.
and she never went back.

977
01:04:19.105 --> 01:04:21.065
The prosecutor would alert us

978
01:04:21.148 --> 01:04:23.192
to what they were gonna show
in the courtroom.

979
01:04:23.693 --> 01:04:27.071
This is two-tenths of a mile
from the ultimate crash site.

980
01:04:27.154 --> 01:04:29.699
We saw the video for the first time.

981
01:04:31.492 --> 01:04:33.452
You will hear the Camry coming

982
01:04:33.536 --> 01:04:36.497
before you see
the last few seconds before impact.

983
01:04:37.123 --> 01:04:39.250
-Oh my gosh.
-It was torture.

984
01:04:39.333 --> 01:04:41.752
And you kept saying
it was like a bomb went off.

985
01:04:41.836 --> 01:04:44.255
-Yeah. it was like a torpedo.
-A missile.

986
01:04:51.554 --> 01:04:52.930
-Brutal.
-Mm-hmm.

987
01:04:53.014 --> 01:04:54.015
Brutal.

988
01:04:54.724 --> 01:04:57.184
That's embedded.
You never get rid of that.

989
01:04:58.811 --> 01:05:03.190
There was a pause. and my wife. Jaime.

990
01:05:03.858 --> 01:05:05.693
went into the bathroom and threw up.

991
01:05:06.569 --> 01:05:12.116
100% acceleration
through the entire final five seconds.

992
01:05:14.869 --> 01:05:19.081
No service brake was deployed
during that final five seconds.

993
01:05:19.582 --> 01:05:22.293
-What other explanation do you have?
-100 miles an hour.

994
01:05:22.376 --> 01:05:25.254
100% acceleration. Never hit a brake.

995
01:05:25.338 --> 01:05:28.341
It was a big slap in the face.
thinking we're there for her

996
01:05:28.424 --> 01:05:32.303
'cause we feel bad for her too.
and then it's all a lie.

997
01:05:35.765 --> 01:05:38.100
It's day two
in the trial of the Strongsville teen

998
01:05:38.184 --> 01:05:40.895
charged with murder in a deadly crash.

999
01:05:42.146 --> 01:05:44.357
When I first got this case

1000
01:05:45.358 --> 01:05:47.318
and saw that the charge was murder.

1001
01:05:47.902 --> 01:05:52.323
I thought to myself.
"Boy. if she's driving the car.

1002
01:05:52.406 --> 01:05:56.327
and it was her purpose
to kill these people.

1003
01:05:56.410 --> 01:05:58.621
she must have wanted to kill herself too."

1004
01:06:01.749 --> 01:06:04.710
In fact. we know
that she was not suicidal.

1005
01:06:05.628 --> 01:06:09.173
I would never. ever see her
purposely wanting to hurt herself.

1006
01:06:09.256 --> 01:06:11.550
Say that is.
and she's so sad. like mentally.

1007
01:06:11.634 --> 01:06:13.719
I… I don't think that's the way to do it.

1008
01:06:14.637 --> 01:06:16.764
Kenzie loves herself a lot.

1009
01:06:16.847 --> 01:06:19.976
She wouldn't even have a McChicken
with me at McDonald's

1010
01:06:20.059 --> 01:06:22.144
because she cared so much
about her own health.

1011
01:06:22.228 --> 01:06:24.897
I don't feel like somebody like that.

1012
01:06:24.981 --> 01:06:28.109
who's caring so much about their body
and so much about

1013
01:06:29.110 --> 01:06:31.195
themselves and how they're doing.

1014
01:06:31.278 --> 01:06:32.863
would be suicidal.

1015
01:06:33.948 --> 01:06:35.324
Her birthday was coming up.

1016
01:06:35.408 --> 01:06:39.203
She had an expensive designer outfit
ready to wear.

1017
01:06:40.538 --> 01:06:43.165
She had presents ready.
wrapped up from Dom.

1018
01:06:43.249 --> 01:06:44.959
that she still has never opened.

1019
01:06:45.751 --> 01:06:48.921
Nothing makes sense. It really doesn't.

1020
01:06:49.588 --> 01:06:53.676
Mr. McDonnell brought up the issue
of her trying to kill herself.

1021
01:06:53.759 --> 01:06:55.594
How could anybody do that?

1022
01:06:55.678 --> 01:07:00.391
Everybody that's heard this evidence
can't figure out

1023
01:07:00.474 --> 01:07:02.685
how could anybody do that.

1024
01:07:02.768 --> 01:07:05.813
We don't have to prove
that she was suicidal.

1025
01:07:05.896 --> 01:07:08.107
but she put that car into the wall.

1026
01:07:08.190 --> 01:07:10.484
and the results were as foreseeable

1027
01:07:10.568 --> 01:07:13.446
as if she drove that car
off of the Grand Canyon.

1028
01:07:14.196 --> 01:07:16.157
Is it just kids being kids?

1029
01:07:16.240 --> 01:07:18.492
Is it Dominic grabbing the steering wheel?

1030
01:07:19.285 --> 01:07:20.995
Those are all possibilities.

1031
01:07:21.996 --> 01:07:25.583
What do you think happened
to cause the crash?

1032
01:07:26.375 --> 01:07:28.544
Through all the evidence
that has been presented.

1033
01:07:28.627 --> 01:07:32.840
the most logical speculation
seems to be a medical emergency.

1034
01:07:34.467 --> 01:07:36.427
I always tell everybody that she has POTS.

1035
01:07:37.678 --> 01:07:41.223
POTS stands for postural orthostatic
tachycardia syndrome.

1036
01:07:41.724 --> 01:07:44.643
It's a blood pressure disorder.

1037
01:07:44.727 --> 01:07:49.523
You can either get dizzy. lightheadedness.
you can black out.

1038
01:07:49.607 --> 01:07:52.485
With POTS. you just black out.

1039
01:07:52.568 --> 01:07:54.320
It can happen very fast.

1040
01:07:54.403 --> 01:07:57.656
If I move a certain way.
it just comes out of nowhere.

1041
01:07:57.740 --> 01:08:00.910
I could just be sitting like this.
and it could hit me.

1042
01:08:03.079 --> 01:08:05.748
You can move the microphone.
It goes side to side.

1043
01:08:05.831 --> 01:08:06.832
Okay.

1044
01:08:13.964 --> 01:08:16.842
Can you state your name
and spell your last name for the record?

1045
01:08:16.926 --> 01:08:19.929
Natalie Shirilla. S-H-I-R-I-L-L-A.

1046
01:08:20.012 --> 01:08:23.974
When was Mackenzie diagnosed with POTS?

1047
01:08:24.058 --> 01:08:25.226
2017.

1048
01:08:25.309 --> 01:08:28.229
And so you were aware
of these POTS incidents.

1049
01:08:28.312 --> 01:08:33.484
yet you still went to the BMV and said.
"Give my daughter a… a driver's license."

1050
01:08:33.567 --> 01:08:34.401
Yes.

1051
01:08:34.485 --> 01:08:36.028
But as a mom.

1052
01:08:36.529 --> 01:08:39.573
this thing is so serious to you. correct?

1053
01:08:40.074 --> 01:08:40.908
It can be.

1054
01:08:40.991 --> 01:08:45.746
You never told her not to drive the car
because of this POTS diagnosis?

1055
01:08:45.830 --> 01:08:47.540
She's been able to manage it.

1056
01:08:47.623 --> 01:08:50.126
You're here to tell us
that this was the reason

1057
01:08:50.209 --> 01:08:52.294
that she crashed the car
into the PLIDCO building.

1058
01:08:52.378 --> 01:08:54.380
Isn't that the…
Isn't that the bottom line?

1059
01:08:54.880 --> 01:08:56.090
It… It could be.

1060
01:08:56.173 --> 01:08:57.967
-Could it be?
-It could be.

1061
01:08:59.552 --> 01:09:02.263
-No further questions. Your Honor.
-Redirect.

1062
01:09:02.888 --> 01:09:04.431
-That's it?
-Yep.

1063
01:09:05.432 --> 01:09:08.269
If that was an obvious element of defense.

1064
01:09:08.894 --> 01:09:14.817
we were never provided with a opinion
from a medical person

1065
01:09:15.526 --> 01:09:17.403
stating that Mackenzie had suffered

1066
01:09:17.486 --> 01:09:20.865
some kind of POTS incident
that caused this.

1067
01:09:21.365 --> 01:09:24.827
Um… And I think that's because

1068
01:09:25.536 --> 01:09:26.829
that's not what happened.

1069
01:09:28.581 --> 01:09:30.374
It's physically impossible.

1070
01:09:30.457 --> 01:09:33.794
If she passed out. then her foot
would have eased off the gas.

1071
01:09:33.878 --> 01:09:36.839
-Wouldn't have stuck down like that.
-It makes no sense whatsoever.

1072
01:09:38.924 --> 01:09:42.636
Mackenzie drove that car down Progress.

1073
01:09:42.720 --> 01:09:45.806
going up to 100 miles an hour.

1074
01:09:46.307 --> 01:09:51.562
This would have taken intense engagement
with the steering and controls of that car

1075
01:09:51.645 --> 01:09:54.356
just because of the nature
of the turns on the road.

1076
01:09:54.857 --> 01:09:58.152
There's an S-curve.
and it goes up. and then it goes down.

1077
01:09:59.612 --> 01:10:03.240
That is not a piece of road
that someone could navigate

1078
01:10:03.324 --> 01:10:06.577
at 100 miles an hour while blacked out.

1079
01:10:11.540 --> 01:10:16.754
How does a medical emergency
account for the control of the car?

1080
01:10:19.840 --> 01:10:23.844
I'm unsure. I have… 'Cause I have
no recollection of that morning.

1081
01:10:23.928 --> 01:10:26.430
But I know
nothing about it was intentional

1082
01:10:26.513 --> 01:10:28.182
'cause that's not in my character.

1083
01:10:31.268 --> 01:10:32.937
Please state your full name.

1084
01:10:33.020 --> 01:10:35.439
I'm Christine Russo. I'm Dominic's mother.

1085
01:10:35.522 --> 01:10:41.612
Did you. at any point. um.
provide the Strongsville Police Department

1086
01:10:41.695 --> 01:10:44.865
with some videos that you had obtained

1087
01:10:44.949 --> 01:10:48.410
that had conversations
between Mackenzie and Dominic?

1088
01:10:48.494 --> 01:10:49.328
Yes.

1089
01:10:49.411 --> 01:10:53.249
And how did you
come into possession of those videos?

1090
01:10:53.332 --> 01:10:58.837
They were recorded on a phone
that happened to be in my son's home.

1091
01:11:00.172 --> 01:11:04.843
Christine Russo had brought
to the investigators' attention

1092
01:11:04.927 --> 01:11:10.140
some recordings made by Dominic
just a matter of days before the crash.

1093
01:11:11.433 --> 01:11:13.602
Dom. open the door.

1094
01:11:14.853 --> 01:11:17.314
I can't open the door.
I can't sit here and fight.

1095
01:11:17.398 --> 01:11:20.651
We gotta go to dinner
to see my grandparents. I can't…

1096
01:11:20.734 --> 01:11:23.237
You're not going to dinner
if you don't open the door.

1097
01:11:23.320 --> 01:11:24.738
I'ma let you know that now.

1098
01:11:24.822 --> 01:11:26.740
You're gonna come open this door right now

1099
01:11:26.824 --> 01:11:29.451
or there's gonna be
a serious fucking problem.

1100
01:11:31.161 --> 01:11:35.040
Okay. ready? I'm gonna count to ten.
The door's gonna open. okay?

1101
01:11:35.124 --> 01:11:37.501
You're gonna open the door
and stop hiding behind the door

1102
01:11:37.584 --> 01:11:39.420
like a little fucking bitch.

1103
01:11:39.503 --> 01:11:42.006
Step away from the door.
Maybe I can come outside and talk.

1104
01:11:42.089 --> 01:11:43.757
No. we're not fighting outside.

1105
01:11:43.841 --> 01:11:46.468
You're gonna open the door right now.

1106
01:11:46.552 --> 01:11:48.971
-Why aren't we fighting outside?
-One minute.

1107
01:11:49.054 --> 01:11:51.390
Now my mom's trying to call me. I gotta--

1108
01:11:51.473 --> 01:11:53.851
No. If you hang up on me.
we're done. I'm leaving.

1109
01:11:55.019 --> 01:11:57.938
-Kenzie. there's nothing I can do.
-There is.

1110
01:11:58.022 --> 01:11:59.189
Stop being a little bitch.

1111
01:11:59.273 --> 01:12:01.108
I can't let you in with how you're acting.

1112
01:12:01.191 --> 01:12:02.401
It's as simple as that.

1113
01:12:02.484 --> 01:12:04.778
Okay. I'm gonna
break into your house. then.

1114
01:12:05.529 --> 01:12:07.948
Dude. what the hell? What the actual fuck?

1115
01:12:09.325 --> 01:12:12.911
You don't let me in the house
that I sleep in every night. we are done.

1116
01:12:16.957 --> 01:12:19.251
-I was disgusted. and I really think that…
-Yeah.

1117
01:12:19.335 --> 01:12:20.919
It just really made me mad.

1118
01:12:21.628 --> 01:12:25.132
Yeah. I felt sorry for Dominic.
I can't believe he didn't say anything.

1119
01:12:26.175 --> 01:12:28.135
Had you ever seen that side to her?

1120
01:12:28.218 --> 01:12:29.678
-No.
-Nope.

1121
01:12:30.763 --> 01:12:33.265
Didn't see that side of her at all.

1122
01:12:34.183 --> 01:12:36.810
How would you describe
Dominic's tone on these videos?

1123
01:12:36.894 --> 01:12:38.020
Very calm.

1124
01:12:38.103 --> 01:12:41.398
How would you describe
the defendant's tone on these videos?

1125
01:12:41.482 --> 01:12:42.649
Irate and angry.

1126
01:12:43.609 --> 01:12:45.402
Thank you. I have no further questions.

1127
01:12:46.653 --> 01:12:49.782
You could sense a mood in the courtroom.

1128
01:12:49.865 --> 01:12:52.451
It was as if people
were coming to the realization

1129
01:12:52.951 --> 01:12:55.496
that she could actually do it.

1130
01:12:55.579 --> 01:12:57.623
She was volatile enough

1131
01:12:58.123 --> 01:13:00.876
and angry enough

1132
01:13:01.377 --> 01:13:04.463
and desperate enough…
to do just about anything.

1133
01:13:06.799 --> 01:13:11.011
When that came out.
there was no hiding who you were anymore.

1134
01:13:11.887 --> 01:13:14.098
It just all painted a huge picture.

1135
01:13:15.933 --> 01:13:19.144
She actually intentionally murdered him.

1136
01:13:23.232 --> 01:13:26.443
This catastrophe took place

1137
01:13:26.527 --> 01:13:30.280
at the conclusion
of a rocky and tumultuous relationship

1138
01:13:30.364 --> 01:13:34.159
between Mackenzie Shirilla
and Dominic Russo.

1139
01:13:34.868 --> 01:13:39.415
Whatever happened. Judge.
was because of that relationship.

1140
01:13:39.498 --> 01:13:42.251
That is why this took place.

1141
01:13:42.751 --> 01:13:44.461
And what about Davion?

1142
01:13:45.796 --> 01:13:47.714
He's just cargo in the backseat.

1143
01:13:48.215 --> 01:13:50.634
If you knew
you were gonna kill your boyfriend.

1144
01:13:50.717 --> 01:13:52.594
what did Davion have to do with that?

1145
01:13:53.095 --> 01:13:54.596
He had nothing to do with that.

1146
01:13:54.680 --> 01:13:57.391
You could have let him out.
let him walk away.

1147
01:13:57.474 --> 01:14:01.061
She treated him with the utmost disregard.

1148
01:14:02.187 --> 01:14:05.524
We trust the court. and we wait
for your verdict. Thank you. Your Honor.

1149
01:14:05.607 --> 01:14:07.734
We ask you to find her guilty
on all counts.

1150
01:14:16.410 --> 01:14:19.913
There is nothing
that I can do or say today

1151
01:14:19.997 --> 01:14:23.208
that will return these two young men
to their families.

1152
01:14:25.377 --> 01:14:29.381
This trial is the culmination
of decisions made by one person.

1153
01:14:31.049 --> 01:14:32.426
The crash video.

1154
01:14:33.385 --> 01:14:37.723
The video clearly shows
purpose and intent of the defendant.

1155
01:14:38.223 --> 01:14:41.518
She chose a course of death
and destruction that day.

1156
01:14:42.019 --> 01:14:46.773
She morphs from a responsible driver
to literal hell on wheels

1157
01:14:46.857 --> 01:14:49.109
as she makes her way down the street.

1158
01:14:50.194 --> 01:14:52.196
Court renders the following verdicts.

1159
01:14:52.696 --> 01:14:53.780
Count one.

1160
01:14:54.364 --> 01:14:57.618
The court. having had count one tried
to a pursuant to waiver.

1161
01:14:57.701 --> 01:14:59.786
finds the defendant Mackenzie Shirilla

1162
01:14:59.870 --> 01:15:02.706
guilty of murder. to wit. Dominic Russo.

1163
01:15:02.789 --> 01:15:07.419
in violation of Ohio Revised Code
section 2903.02a.

1164
01:15:07.503 --> 01:15:09.338
is charged with count one.

1165
01:15:09.421 --> 01:15:10.714
Count two.

1166
01:15:10.797 --> 01:15:14.676
The court. having had count two tried
to a pursuant to waiver.

1167
01:15:14.760 --> 01:15:17.721
finds the defendant Mackenzie Shirilla
guilty of murder.

1168
01:15:17.804 --> 01:15:19.306
to wit. Davion Flanagan.

1169
01:15:19.389 --> 01:15:24.520
in violation of Ohio Revised Code
Section 2903.02a.

1170
01:15:24.603 --> 01:15:26.688
is charged with count two
of the indictment.

1171
01:15:28.857 --> 01:15:30.526
-Mom?
-Hey. hey.

1172
01:15:30.609 --> 01:15:32.819
-Oh my goodness.
-I know. Kenzie.

1173
01:15:32.903 --> 01:15:35.531
I didn't think
that was gonna happen. She was just like…

1174
01:15:35.614 --> 01:15:38.158
She just made it seem
like I was just a murderer.

1175
01:15:38.242 --> 01:15:39.826
I know. I know. sweetie.

1176
01:15:40.327 --> 01:15:41.578
I was. like. shocked.

1177
01:15:42.204 --> 01:15:44.039
I genuinely do not think

1178
01:15:44.122 --> 01:15:47.417
that this could have been on purpose.
intentional. or planned.

1179
01:15:47.501 --> 01:15:49.711
Like. it doesn't make sense to me.

1180
01:15:50.712 --> 01:15:52.130
We were all friends.

1181
01:15:55.926 --> 01:15:59.972
A local case has drawn
national and international attention.

1182
01:16:00.055 --> 01:16:04.851
Sentencing will take place tomorrow
for 19-year-old Mackenzie Shirilla.

1183
01:16:04.935 --> 01:16:07.771
Mackenzie Shirilla could face
up to life in prison.

1184
01:16:08.772 --> 01:16:11.358
How much time do you think I'm gonna get?

1185
01:16:12.109 --> 01:16:14.027
I'm sure they're gonna go with the max.

1186
01:16:14.611 --> 01:16:16.071
-The max?
-Okay?

1187
01:16:17.030 --> 01:16:20.075
A conviction for murder
carries a life sentence.

1188
01:16:20.158 --> 01:16:23.829
The sentencing judge chooses
between 15 years to life

1189
01:16:23.912 --> 01:16:27.874
or 30 years to life
before the possibility of parole.

1190
01:16:29.960 --> 01:16:35.841
I just wanted my son's life
to have… concrete value

1191
01:16:35.924 --> 01:16:37.467
in the term of years.

1192
01:16:38.093 --> 01:16:40.887
And if that was 15. okay.

1193
01:16:40.971 --> 01:16:44.266
If that was 30.
I would be happier with that.

1194
01:16:45.726 --> 01:16:48.604
We have received a series of letters

1195
01:16:48.687 --> 01:16:51.023
that have been submitted
on behalf of the defendant.

1196
01:16:51.523 --> 01:16:56.111
They describe her as a good student
